    <h1>Your plentymarkets account</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The menu <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong> contains information about your plentymarkets system and possibilities for configuring the system. You can use the Service Centre to make changes to your system, e.g. book modules, order domains and subdomains or change your contract.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">States of development and version updates</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>plentymarkets is constantly updated and optimised. The version life cycle of plentymarkets consists of the states of development <strong>Beta</strong>, <strong>Early</strong> und <strong>Stable</strong>. By default, your system is set to the <strong>Stable</strong> version. However, if you want to benefit from improvements and new features earlier, you can set your system to a version with <a href="/en/basics/admin-tasks/version-cycle">an earlier state of development</a>. Your current version of plentymarkets is displayed in your plentymarkets back end when you point your cursor at the login icon.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A beta version, an early version and a stable version normally are released once a week. You system is updated automatically when a new version is published. The plentymarkets changelog lists the changes made for each update. You can find this changelog in the plentymarkets Forum in the <a href="https://forum.plentymarkets.com/c/changelog" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Changelog</a> category. We recommend that you subscribe to this category. You will then be notified whenever a new changelog entry is published.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="10">1. Accessing the Service Centre</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to access the Service Centre.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Accessing the Service Centre:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="20">2. Changing contract information</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The menu <strong>Start » Service Centre » Tab: Contract</strong> provides you with information about your current plentymarkets contract. In this menu, you can make changes to or cancel your contract.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="30">2.1. Changing your contract</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>plentymarkets grows along with your needs. Decide for yourself how many orders you want to process with plentymarkets each month. We will provide you with the necessary system performance. The <strong>Contract</strong> tab allows you to make changes in your plentymarkets contract on your own once it is up and running. It makes sense to make changes to your contract e.g. if you generate more orders than are included in your current rate. It is possible to book a higher rate at any time. If you book a lower rate, the change will go into effect once the regular duration of your current contract has ended.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Changing the contract:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Contract</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Open configurator</strong> or, if desired, on <strong>Switch to PRO</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Make changes to the contract information as desired.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="40">2.2. Cancelling a contract</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>Contract</strong> tab in the Service Centre also contains an option for cancelling your contract with plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Cancelling a contract:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Contract</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Cancel contract</strong> to request that your contract be cancelled.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="50">3. Managing domain data</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can manage your domain in the <strong>Start » Service Centre » Tab: Domain</strong> menu. The parameters of your domain are shown here. You can also change some of these parameters. You can also order a new domain here or relocate an existing domain. Furthermore, you can link an existing external domain or create a subdomain for a main domain.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock warning">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-warning" title="Warning"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Availability after initial setup or changes</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It can take up to 24 hours until all of the settings are available on all systems. If settings are changed after 4 p.m., the changes will not be processed until after 4 p.m. the following day. If settings are changed on the weekend, these changes will not be processed until after 4 p.m. the following Monday. It can take up to 12 hours to process these changes.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="60">3.1. Information about domains</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><a href="#table-account-domains">Table 1</a> includes explanations of the various domain types.</p>
</div>
