<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="70">3.1.1. Ordering a new domain</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to order a new domain.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Ordering a new domain:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Domain</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Order a new domain</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the desired domain name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the top level domain (TLD) from the drop-down list, e.g. <strong>co.uk</strong> or <strong>com</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Check</strong>.<br>
→ The system checks if the domain is available.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You will also receive information about how much it costs to use the domain per month. Enter the contact details (domain handle) and assign the corresponding plentymarkets system. Then order the domain by clicking on <strong>Place order</strong>.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Registering .com domains</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You will receive an email when registering a .com domain. This email will ask you to confirm the WHOIS data that was entered. This email is sent to the email address that was entered under ADMIN-C in the handle data (WHOIS). If you do not receive an email, check that the email address is available and working.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="80">3.1.2. Relocating a domain</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If the domain is already available, you can relocate it. To do so, proceed as described in the chapter <strong>Ordering a new domain</strong>. Follow the instructions in the menu. Also note the following information regarding domain transfers:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Have your current provider’s authentication code ready as you will need to enter this code.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The processing times may vary depending on the Top Level Domain.</p>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>For <strong>.de</strong> domains: up to 24 hours</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>For <strong>.com</strong> and <strong>.net</strong> domains: 3 to 7 days</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>For <strong>.eu</strong> domains: up to 5 days</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<p>You will receive an email if you relocate a <strong>.com</strong> or <strong>.net</strong> domain. The email will ask you to confirm the relocation. This email is sent to the email address that was entered under ADMIN-C in the handle data (WHOIS). If you do not receive an email, check that the email address is available and working. If the email address no longer exists, then ask your current domain provider to change the email address.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="90">3.1.3. Creating an external domain</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the option <strong>Create a new external domain</strong> to link an existing external domain to a plentymarkets system. The domain’s IP address will be displayed in the overview of domains. Next, save the DNS data in the DNS zone of the hosting service provider. To find this DNS information, go to the Service Centre and open the newly created external domain. The DNS data is shown in the <strong>Current DNS settings</strong> area. If there is an IPv6 A Record in your externally managed domain, then remove this IPv6 A-Record.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="100">3.1.4. Ordering a subdomain</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can create as many subdomains as you want for a domain. You do not need to register these subdomains. For example, if you have the domain <strong>yourstore.com</strong>, then you could create the subdomain <strong>info.yourstore.com</strong> to provide special information about your online store with this domain. Use the drop-down list to select which main domain you want to link with the subdomain. Select the corresponding plentymarkets system as well.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Availability and updates</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It can take up to 24 hours for new domains or changes to become available. This is because the servers need to be restarted periodically and the data is not distributed in the cloud immediately.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="110">3.1.5. Deleting a subdomain</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can delete a subdomain. To do so, proceed as described below.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting a subdomain:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>. <br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Domain</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the subdomain.<br>
→ The subdomain details are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete subdomain</strong>.<br>
→ The subdomain is deleted from the system.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="120">3.2. Saving the domain handle</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You need to save the contact details of the domain owner in the <strong>Domain handle</strong> area.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Saving the domain handle:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Domain</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Domain handle</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the contact details of the domain owner.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="130">3.3. Cancelling a domain</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to cancel a domain.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock warning">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-warning" title="Warning"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Cancelling the main domain</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Only cancel your main domain if you also want to cancel your plentymarkets system’s contract. Otherwise, you will have to save a new main domain.<br>
If you want to cancel your system contract, also pay attention to our cancellation deadlines. If you cancel your main domain too early, the domain’s contract might well end earlier than the system’s contract. The system will no longer be available in this case, even though the contract has not ended yet.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Cancelling the domain:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
