</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="230">3.11. Saving the CNAME Resource Record</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A Canonical Name or CNAME record is a type of DNS record that links an alias name to another canonical domain name. For example, you can use it along with the provider <strong>Shopgate</strong> to create a mobile version of your online store or you can use it to set up an external email service. In the example, the source <em>mobile.your-shop.com</em> is the mobile version of the domain <em>your-shop.com</em>. Use the Shopgate subdomain <em>cname.shopgate.com</em> as the target. This CNAME entry ensures that your store will have the correct resolution with Shopgate.</p>
</div>
