</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="ssl-certificate">4. Managing the SSL certificate</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This chapter provides you with information about SSL certificates. You will find out how to check for the expiration date of your SSL certificate and how to order a new SSL certificate or deactivate your active SSL certificate if necessary.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="280">4.1. What is an SSL certificate?</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>An SSL certificate is used to encrypt your website. A SSL certificate also provides a secure connection to your website and online store. An SSL certificate is required for certain markets and for receiving the Trusted Shops certification. Your customers can see when you are using an SSL certificate as your website will be accessed via <em>https</em>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>SSL certificates are offered by independent certificate providers. plentymarkets offers two types of SSL certificates:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>You can buy a SSL certificate which is valid for at least a year. This certificate is not renewed. After the SSL certificate expires, you need to order a new certificate.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>You can order a free SSL certificate from <a href="https://letsencrypt.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Let’s Encrypt</a>. It is renewed automatically and can be terminated with one month notice.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You order the SSL certificate for your <a href="/en/basics/admin-tasks/plentymarkets-account#domain">main domain</a>, i.e. the one that you set as the main domain in the <strong>Start » Service Centre » Tab: Domain</strong> menu (image 2, blue arrow). If you want to use an SSL certificate for a different domain, you will have to set this domain as your main domain first.</p>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/assets/ENG-Start-pm-Konto-Cache02-SI.png" alt="plentymarkets Service center; domains">
</div>
<div class="title">Figure 2. plentymarkets Service center; domains</div>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">No SSL certificates for cancelled domains or test domains</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You cannot order SSL certificates for cancelled domains or for start-up domains and test domains, i.e. domains with names that contain <em>plenty-testdrive.eu</em>, <em>plentymarkets-x1.com</em> etc. For this reason, the <strong>Order SSL certificate</strong> button is not displayed for these types of domains.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="360">4.2. SSL certificate for external domains</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A domain can be hosted externally. The <a href="/en/basics/admin-tasks/plentymarkets-account#150">DNS settings then have to be saved with the external provider of the domain</a>. However, the SSL certificate needs to be saved close to the system. This means that even if the domain is hosted externally, the actual encoding is done directly in the system after the domain forwarding via IP address is carried out. As such, it is not possible to use an external SSL certificate. The SSL certificate needs to be ordered from plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="290">4.3. Prerequisites for booking an SSL certificate</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Before booking an SSL certificate, ensure that the following prerequisites are met:</p>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="_domain">4.3.1. Domain</h4>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>The domain for which you want to order the SSL certificate must be a <a href="/en/basics/admin-tasks/plentymarkets-account#210a">main domain</a> that has been activated in the plentymarkets Service Centre.<br>
→ Check the settings in the plentymarkets Service Centre.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="_active_autoscaling">4.3.2. Active autoscaling</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A few system have not been switched to <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/">autoscaling</a> (AS). In most cases, this is because the domain is not hosted by plentymarkets. As such, the domain owner must adjust the DNS settings manually.<br>
Another cause might be that the domain was added to a client for the first time. These clients are not automatically switched to autoscaling. Instead, the plentymarkets support staff need to switch activate autoscaling manually.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to check if autoscaling is active:</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Checking the autoscaling status:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>*plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Domain</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue plus icon next to the domain to view the DNS settings.<br>
→ The DNS settings are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the column <strong>DNS Record Type</strong>, check if a CNAME entry exists.<br>
→ If a CNAME entry exists, autoscaling is active.<br>
→ If no CNAME entry exists but two A records, autoscaling is not active.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>If autoscaling is not active, contact the plentymarkets Support via the Link:https://forum.plentymarkets.com/t/46996/[plentymarkets Forum] and ask them to activate autoscaling. The thread is in German, but support staff also speaks English.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="_for_subdomains_existing_parent_domain">4.3.3. For subdomains: Existing parent domain</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you want to order an SSL certificate for a subdomain, the parent domain must also exist in the system. In addition, the relationship between domain and subdomain must be entered correctly in the Service Centre.<br>
→ Check the settings in the plentymarkets Service Centre.<br>
→ If you deleted the parent domain from the Service Centre, create the parent domain. If you do not want this parent domain to point to plentymarkets, save an external A record for the parent domain by <a href="/en/basics/admin-tasks/plentymarkets-account#210a">creating a system link</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="_for_external_domains_dns_settings">4.3.4. For external domains: DNS settings</h4>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>The <a href="/en/basics/admin-tasks/plentymarkets-account#150">DNS settings saved with the external provider</a> must be identical to the DNS settings of the plentymarkets Service Center.<br>
→ Check the settings in the service area of your domain provider.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>No IPv6 entry (AAAA record) must exist for the domain.<br>
→ Check the settings in the service area of your domain provider.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Any existing CAA records for the domain must allow ordering the selected certificate.<br>
→ Check the settings in the service area of your domain provider.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="300">4.4. Managing a bought SSL certificate</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you buy an SSL certificate, you need to order a new SSL certificate before your old certificate expires. This means that even if you already own an SSL certificate that is about to expire, you still select a certificate provider and duration from scratch. That means that you need to select a certificate provider and the certification duration every time you order an SSL certificate. plentymarkets orders the SSL certificate on your behalf and bills you for the one-off purchase price and the monthly fee.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="310">4.4.1. Checking the expiration date of a SSL certificate</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to view the expiration date of a SSL certificate.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Checking the expiration date of a SSL certificate:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » System settings » Client » Select client » SSL</strong>.<br>
→ A table with the domain’s certificates is displayed.<br>
→ The row <strong>Expiration date</strong> shows the date on which the certificate expires.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="320">4.4.2. Buying an SSL certificate</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to order a SSL certificate.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Buying an SSL certificate:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » System settings » Client » Select client » SSL</strong>.<br>
→ The domain’s certificates are displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the row <strong>Order new SSL for domain: [domain name]</strong>, click on the down arrow to the right.<br>
→ The SSL certificates that are available for the domain are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Check the SSL certificates available for booking.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Order SSL</strong> in the line of the SSL certificate that you want to order.<br>
→ The SSL certificate is ordered.<br>
<strong>*<em>_Note:</em></strong> It can take up to 2 hours for the SSL certificate to be activated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Delete the browser cache.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Delete the DNS cache.</p>
<div class="olist loweralpha">
<ol class="loweralpha" type="a">
<li>
<p>Click the shortcut key <strong>Windows key + R</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter <code>CMD</code> and press <strong>Enter</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the command <code>ipconfig /flushdns</code>.<br>
→ The DNS cache is cleared.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="330">4.4.3. Deactivating a bought SSL certificate</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can temporarily or permanently deactivate an active SSL certificate. To do so, proceed as described below.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Expiration date remains the same</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The total validity period of your SSL certificate is not extended when it is temporarily deactivated.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deactivating a bought SSL certificate:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Domain</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the main domain.<br>
→ The expiration date of the SSL certificate is shown in the <strong>SSL certificate</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Deactivate SSL certificate</strong>.<br>
→ Your SSL certificate is deactivated.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>You can reactivate your SSL certificate at any time by clicking on the <strong>Activate SSL certificate</strong> button.<br>
<strong><em>Note:</em></strong> It can take up to 4 hours for the SSL certificate to be activated.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="340">4.5. Managing a free Let’s Encrypt SSL certificate</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Instead of buying an SSL certificate, you can also chose an SSL certificate provided by the certification authority <a href="https://letsencrypt.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Let’s Encrypt</a>. The certificates are renewed automatically and can be terminated with a month’s notice. Proceed as described below to activate a free SSL certificate of the certificate provider Let’s Encrypt.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Provisioning fee</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Let’s Encrypt SSL certificates are free of charge. When you book an SSL certificate of Let’s Encrypt, all you pay is a monthly provisioning fee to plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="350">4.5.1. Activating a free Let’s Encrypt certificate</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to activate a free SSL certificate of the certificate provider Let’s Encrypt.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating a free SSL certificate:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Domain</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the main domain.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>SSL certificate</strong> area, activate the check box <strong>LetsEncypt</strong>.<br>
→ The SSL certificate is activated.<br>
<strong><em>Note:</em></strong> It can take up to 24 hours before the activation takes effect.<br>
→ plentymarkets bills you for the provisioning fee monthly.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="370">5. Managing clients (stores)</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In plentymarkets, the term Client (store) refers to additional online stores that are all managed with the same plentymarkets system as the default store. Existing clients (stores) are shown in the <strong>Start » Service Centre » Tab: Client (store)</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="380">5.1. Ordering a client (store)</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to order a client (store).</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Has the domain been created?</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You need to have a <a href="/en/basics/admin-tasks/plentymarkets-account#domain">domain</a> before you can order a client (store). You have to create this domain beforehand in the <strong>Domain</strong> tab of the main system.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Ordering a client (store):</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Contract</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Open configurator</strong>.<br>
→ The configurator opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Order a client.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="390">5.2. Cancelling a client (store)</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre » Tab: Client (store)</strong> and click on <strong>Cancel client (store)</strong> to cancel a client (store). Confirm the cancellation in the window that is displayed. The start and end of the contract will be displayed.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Ordering a client (store):</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Client (store)</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Cancel client (store)</strong>.<br>
→ A confirmation window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Confirm the cancellation request.<br>
→ The start and end date of your contract is shown.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="400">5.3. Editing the domain settings for clients (stores)</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The tab <strong>Client (store)</strong> also displays information about the domains that are assigned to your clients. Make changes to these settings as described in the chapter <a href="/en/basics/admin-tasks/plentymarkets-account#domain">Domain</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="cache">6. Managing the cache</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The static content of your online store, e.g. item images, are stored in the cache for a certain amount of time. This makes it possible to display such content as quickly as possible. If you make changes, e.g. to an image, then these changes will not go into effect immediately. Rather, they will only become visible once a certain amount of time has passed. It may take up to one hour. Take a look at our <a href="https://www.plentymarkets.eu/blog/Im-Rollout-Mehr-Geschwindigkeit-bei-durchgehender-SSL-Verschluesselung/b-1207/">blog entry</a> on this topic (only available in German).</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="420">6.1. Temporarily deactivating the cache</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can deactivate the cache of your system for a limited time. To do so, proceed as described below.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Temporarily deactivating the cache:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Cache</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the drop-down list <strong>From</strong>, select a start time for deactivating the cache.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the drop-down list <strong>To</strong>, select an end time for deactivating the cache.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Deactivate cache temporarily</strong>.<br>
→ Your system’s cache is deactivated for the selected period of time.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="430">6.2. Permanent SSL redirect</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you booked an SSL certificate, your website will be completely encrypted. The technology SNI/TLS is a common standard that has been used for years. It is supported by all current browsers. However, some of your visitors may use older browsers that do not support this standard. If you deactivate the SSL redirect, then visitors with older browsers will also be able to click through your online store. However, customers will only be able to place an order with current browsers. The order process is always encoded, even if the SSL redirect was deactivated. You can inform customers that it is only possible to place an order with current browsers.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deactivating the permanent SSL redirect:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Cache</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the option <strong>&lt; IE 9 inactive</strong> from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Save permanent SSL redirect</strong>.<br>
→ Your system’s SSL redirect is deactivated.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="440">7. Granting system access to certified agencies</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the menu <strong>Start » Service Centre » Tab: Your agency</strong>, you can grant up to two plentymarkets certified service providers access to specific areas of your system. As such, you allow a design agency and/or a consultant to carry out the following tasks in your plentymarkets system:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Your service provider can delete the cache or temporarily deactivate the cache whilst working on the design in order to work more efficiently.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Your service provider can also view and answer your support tickets. In other words, your service provider can directly communicate with the plentymarkets support staff. Of course, you can still follow along with the discussion yourself.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="450">7.1. Granting access to certified service providers</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to provide the agency and/or the consultant you work with access to the system areas described above:</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Assigning service providers:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Start » Service Centre</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To do so, point your cursor at the plentymarkets logo at the top left of the screen.<br>
→ The Service Centre opens in a new browser tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the blue <strong>plus</strong> icon of the system.<br>
→ The available tabs are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Your agency</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the agency and/or consultant you work with and who you want to provide access for from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The service providers are now linked to your system and have access to the areas mentioned above.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="460">7.2. Screen seen by agencies</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>After you provided your agency access, the agency can access the following information:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Tab <strong>Overview</strong>: The agency has access to the information in your Service Centre under <strong>Tab: Systems » Tab: Overview</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tab <strong>Contract</strong>: Your current rate is shown. However, the agency cannot change your contract details.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tab <strong>Cache</strong>: The agency can delete the cache or temporarily deactivate the cache of your system.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Tab <strong>Tickets</strong>: The service provider has access to the information in the <strong>My account area</strong> under <strong>Tickets</strong>. In other words, the agency’s employees can create and answer tickets.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
